content.detailedDescription: A woman awoke sometime after 3 am, 5/1/00, and immediately notice a greyoval-shaped object hovering above her skylight. bright red and white lights werearrayed across the bottom. within seconds the object descended, rotating slowlyas it proceeded to within such proximity of the roof that its exterior filledthe skylight. [its diameter was thereafter adjudged to be about 25 feet.] alongthe way it tilted radically, revealing triangular shaped lights on its upperportion. the witness noticed a swishing sound associated with the object. shewas either paralyzed in fear or otherwise unable to awaken her husband next toher in the bed. momentarily the object rose and again and moved away. the eventduration was under one minute. afterward, the woman continued to be toofrightened to wake her husband until morning.
content.summary: Oval disc hovers over bedroom skylight in ga.

content.detailedDescription: A man was driving home on i-85 at 12:28 am, 4/24/00, when he observed anairborne object with a pronounced yaw approaching. it was roughly the size of a747 jet and flying slowly s to nw at 1,000-2,000 feet altitude. as he drove byit, he determined the objects outline as an isosceles triangle (the rear sidebeing longer). its exterior was black. it was now hovering directly over agrouping of power lines as the witness drove by. he continued one mile to thenext exit and stopped to view it further. the object seemed to still be hoveringor moving slightly at that point. he noted steady red and bluish-white lightsaround the edges and red "tail lights". two strobe lights near the rear of thebottom strobed in bursts intermittently. presumably the witness then left thearea, though this is not clearly stated. the sighting duration estimated to be 5minutes.
content.summary: Black triangle over i-85 in ga.

content.detailedDescription: A friend and i were fishing at garret lake(night).I always look up when gettingready to cast when i heard the helicopter rotors.Some type of meteor.The objectbegan moving faster and was about 50 meters in front of the hueys and it seem tobe zig zagging in opposition to the first helicopter. the chopper would flyright it would fly left and the reverse is true. after the chopper and objectpassed out of sight (treeline) another chopper in a slower approach flew overthe lake.  all vehicles and object headed south from the north and did notcircle back.The second object i spotted on another night came into my field ofview about a mile and a half a way 60 to 75 degrees traveling horizontally,bright light and it faded in and out. there were no clouds at all and all starswere visible in the night sky.  there was no sound, but the object covered adistance of about 2 miles in about 2.5 seconds. and continued until i lost sight(treeline).
content.summary: Strange lights/choppers over lake garrett, dresden

content.detailedDescription: While in the back yard in the hopes of seeing a meteor shower i saw an objectthat looked identicle to a group, 6-9, of black helium balloons, strungtogether, and moving quickly acroos the sky.  the only difference is instead ofthe balloons being vertical, one atop the other, as would be expected of heliumballoons - they were, and remained, in a fixed horizontal position as it movedto the s/w from the n/e, towards jfk intl airport. no wobble, no sound, nolights.  exactly like balloos but too perfectly a horizontal position26 flight. balloons would have been rising26 the wind was calm which is why the speed26 horizontal travel was odd. unfortunately i have only estimated the month - ido not recall which meteor shower i hoped to see.  may have been leonids, notsure.
content.summary: Dark object flying to the s/w towords jfk airport.

content.detailedDescription: (you can type over theseinstructions.)please limit your narrative to 500 words (equivalent to 1 typedpage). my husband and i were driving along the highway when i spotted the objectto my left above the trees. it was silver-colored and spherical in nature. ipointed it out to him, noting that it was probably the light shining off aplane, since it shone brightly with a metallic tinge. he nodded and said he sawit as well. it did not appear to be moving as we watched it while still drivingalong the highway. i maintained eye contact with it as long as possible, lookingfor wings or any sort of identification marking3b wondering if it was from any local airport although the nearest one was milesaway. we dont get a lot of air traffic around here and i love planes, so i tendto latch onto anything flying in the sky. a clump of trees obscured our view ofthe object for a few seconds and when the area came back into sight it haddisappeared. i looked around the sky for where the plane had gone to, but couldnot see anything at all. my husband who grew up in this area noted that he wassure it was not any local antenna or reflective surfaces he knew of. inaddition, he is an air force veteran and agreed that it was unlike any plane hehad ever seen in the air. only after it had disappeared did we wonder if it hadactually been an ufo and agreed that it was highly likely, given thecircumstances and the fact that we could not see any other objects in the sky.
content.summary: Ufo sighting

content.detailedDescription: Two women observed a bright stationary object in the distance with an apparentsize of one-fourth of the full moon. a deputy sheriff joined them and agreedthat the object appeared anomalous. through a camcorders viewfinder, the objecthad a bell shape with a bluish white body, a broad rim at the bottom, andsequentially pulsating red, white and blue lights at or near the rim. after 70minutes, the object moved slowly and laterally for 2-3 minutes before being lostfrom view in the distance.
content.summary: Prolonged presence of bell-shaped object in mi.

content.detailedDescription: A nearly blind man observed an apparently odd red light near his rural home andcalled his wife out. she viewed a bulbous disc with a flat top and bottom (i.E.,like inverted bowls) moving very slowly below treetop level between 25 and 50yards away. a series of rectangular windows in its upper and lower hemisphereswere separated by narrow black partitions. within the upper portion, a red lightslowly brightened and dimmed. a red band of steady red light separated itshemisphere.The object continued to move slowly into the distance until lost from view.Duration estimated to be 15 minutes.
content.summary: Disc like "inverted bowls" in pa.

content.detailedDescription: In april or may 1970, a teen couple was returning to the girls home afterwatching a softball game. in a rural area between two small ga towns, the boywhile driving suddenly noticed a white glowing ovoid just above pine trees tohis left, pacing the car. a white beam from the object shone down through thetrees. he immediately sped faster, reaching 100 mph attempting to get away, butthe object continued to pace the car. the girl climbed into the rear seat andobserved the object through the side window. she estimated its size at about 20feet in length. no structure was visible within the glowing outline. no soundwas detected from the object at any time.They momentarily lost sight of it, then their car was bathed in white light fromabove. a moment later they again spotted the object about 300 feet behind themand 10 feet above the road, still pacing their speed. when the headlights of anoncoming auto became visible to them, they looked back to discover that theobject was gone. they reached home without further incident but remained intheir vehicle for many minutes to collect themselves.
content.summary: Car paced by glowing oval in ga.

content.detailedDescription: A woman walking near her home observed a cylindrical object nearly overhead atan estimated 30,000 feet altitude. the object appeared faster and larger than ajetliner, had tapered rounded ends, and either glowed white or reflectedsunlight. no contrail was observed. it was lost from view in the distance in8-10 seconds when it appeared to "blink out".
content.summary: Cylindrical object at high altitude over ia farmla

content.detailedDescription: Two boys crossing a footbridge over a creek observed two bright lightsapproaching from the distance at treetop level, criss-crossing the creek as ifsearching. as the lights moved slowly (walking speed) and silently overhead,they detected a dark undetermined shape blocking the stars. the object continuedto follow the creek until lost from view.
content.summary: Dark shape following a creek in mn.

content.detailedDescription: A man and two sons were watching a televised boxing match when a daughter raninside to exclaim that a flying saucer was outside. they ran outside to see itpassing very slowly about 250 feet over their roof. several neighbors outsidewere also observing it. the object was described as a dull grey disc, 30-45 feetin diameter, with about 20 dimly lit yellow squares around it that were assumedto be windows. sounds associated included a faint hum, rumbling ("mechanicalrolling") and a "clunk" each it slowly rotated. it continued on a course eastacross the street, hovered there momentarily, then continued out of view beyondobstructing trees.  two blocks away a woman an son, while driving, observed apparently the sameobject, describing it similarly.Total duration of the event was estimated as five minutes.
content.summary: Domed disc over mn suburb; numerous witnesses.
